cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.FL

The paper deals with formal verification of systems with replicated components, which is a topic that falls under the scope of several arXiv CS sub-categories. The use of CSP as the formalism suggests that the paper could belong to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) or cs.PL (Programming Languages). The focus on parameterised model checking and the use of abstraction methods suggest that the paper could also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper's emphasis on symbolic representation of process behaviour and its generality suggest that it could belong to cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory).
